      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on my psych dissertation and i'm a bit stuck. my results showed a p-value of 0.06 for my main hypothesis. i can see a pretty clear trend in the graph, but technically it's not significant. can you explain why we can't just call that significant? like, what is the actual logic behind that threshold?",
